For C API : read an array of byte from a data block.

Parameters:
reader  data block in which byte is stored
size  number of byte values in the array
ap  variable argument list - the next item is assumed to be a pointer to a pointer to a byte array. This pointer is changed to point to a byte array allocated on the C Heap. Use SBWFree to deallocate this array.

For C API : read a 2D array of bytes from a data block.

Parameters:
reader  data block in which byte array is stored
xSize  set to the number of byte values on the first dimension of the array
ySize  set to the number of byte values on the first dimension of the array
ap  variable argument list - the next item is assumed to be a pointer to a pointer to a unsigned char * array. This pointer is changed to point to an unsigned char * array allocated on the C Heap. Use SBWFree2DArray to deallocate this array.
